***   This is some bibliography associated with   ***
***      SaGA programs and algorithms             ***


  Interpolation, mapping
  ----------------------

  Watson D.F.
Contouring: a practical guide to analysis and display of spacial data.
Pergamon Press, 1992, ISBN 0 08 040286 0
  /A very good book. If you want to learn about contouring
  and interpolation from irregular datasets you definitely
  need to start with it. In many cases it is all you'll need.
  For further information there are plenty of references to 
  other books and papers./


  Daly R.
Atmospheric data analysis.
New York: Cambridge University Press, 1991.

  Ripley B.
Spatial statistics. New York: Wiley 1991.

  Sibson, R., 1981,
A brief description of natural neighbour interpolation, 
in Barnett, V., ed., Interpreting multivariate data: John Wiley,
p. 21.
 /The first introduction of the "natural neighbour interpolation"
 method/.

  Bretherthon F. P., R. E.  Davis,  Fandry
(Objective mapping)

  Franke R., 1982.
Smooth interpolation of scattered data by local thin plate splines.
Computers Math with Applic., V.8, #4, 273-281.

  Franke R., 1982.
Scattered data interpolation: tests of some methods.
Math. Computation, V.38, p. 181-200.

  Briggs I.C., 1984.
Machine contouring using minimal curvature.
Geophysisc, V.39, #1, 39-48.

  Davis J.C. 1981.
Statistical techniques in petroleum explorations.
Commun. Stat-Theor. Meth., V.A10, #15, 1479-1503.

  Davis J.C., 1981.
Contour mapping SURFACE-II.
Science, V. 237, 669-672. 
 
  Marcotte Denis, 1991,
Cokriging with MATLAB.
Computers and Geosciences, v.17, p. 1265-1280.
 


  Computational geometry.
  -----------------------

 Preparata F.P. & M.I. Shamos
Computational geometry: an introduction.
Springer-Verlag, N.-Y., 1985.



